{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "27", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "57", "S": "54"}}, "news": [{"title": "Mumbai: No medical bail to Mid-City Heights' partner in \u20b956 crore real estate fraud", "para": "A Mumbai special court has denied medical bail to businessman Amarjeet Shukla, accused in a Rs 55.71 crore real estate fraud. The court found his medical condition, while needing treatment, did not constitute a life-threatening emergency justifying release from custody. Shukla sought bail for surgery, but the court deemed state facilities adequate.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/mumbai-court-denies-medical-bail-to-real-estate-fraud-accused-in-56-crore-case/130542745?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-88198/130542745.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Mumbai: In a first, SRA starts freezing builders\u2019 sale flats to secure tenants\u2019 rent", "para": "The Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) is now freezing sale flats equivalent to three years' rent to ensure eligible slum dwellers receive their payments and new homes. This measure aims to prevent developers from defaulting on transit rent obligations. The SRA is also pushing for faster project completion and has collected over Rs 1,000 crore in rent.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/mumbai-sra-freezes-builders-sale-flats-to-secure-rent-for-slum-dwellers/130542483?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39482/130542483.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Bombay HC backs housing society, allows new builder after 13-year delay", "para": "The Bombay High Court has dismissed a builder's plea to stop a Wadala housing society from appointing a new developer for redeveloping 46 buildings. The court emphasized that tenants, residing in structures built in 1957, cannot wait indefinitely for safer homes. The builder's challenge cited project delays, but the court prioritized the members' urgent need for redevelopment.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bombay-high-court-supports-housing-society-allows-new-builder-after-years-of-delay/130542452?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-105738/130542452.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}